# The catching of small birds by a method of two people holding a tall cane pole each, with a fishing net strung between them.  Birds flying down a grove of trees become tangled and the net is flung forwards and down.  (Reference: [[w:Robert Graves|Robert Graves]] short story ''The Viscountess and the Short-Haired Girl'' published in ''The Shout and Other Stories'', Penguin, paperback reprint 1978.)